1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,291
[helicopter whirring]

2
00:00:09,375 --> 00:00:11,291
We're reporting live from
the explosion site

3
00:00:11,375 --> 00:00:13,250
in the south eastern area
of Tokyo.

4
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:16,625
Our question is, could this be
a repeat of the Lost?

5
00:00:16,708 --> 00:00:19,375
At the present moment, no
casualties have been reported.

6
00:00:19,458 --> 00:00:22,166
For your safety, we advise
the public to stay indoors

7
00:00:22,250 --> 00:00:24,125
unless it's absolutely
necessary.

8
00:00:24,208 --> 00:00:27,000
-We will remain on the scene...
-[SYUNPEI] Whoa, look at that.

9
00:00:27,083 --> 00:00:29,208
At least it's in
the lock-down district.

10
00:00:29,291 --> 00:00:30,833
I guess we should
all be grateful.

11
00:00:30,916 --> 00:00:33,458
The officers in that precinct
will need backup.

12
00:00:33,541 --> 00:00:35,833
I need more men down there
to get a handle on it.

13
00:00:36,916 --> 00:00:38,000
[door opens]

14
00:00:39,333 --> 00:00:40,708
[RYOKO]
Good luck out there, guys!

15
00:00:40,791 --> 00:00:41,833
[CHIEF]
What're you doing here?

16
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:43,291
Aren't you off today?

17
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:45,833
Oh, I just need
to borrow Syunpei for a bit.

18
00:00:45,916 --> 00:00:47,541
-[SYUNPEI] Huh? For what?
-[CHIEF] Negishi!

19
00:00:47,625 --> 00:00:48,875
[door closes]

20
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:52,208
Hey! Takuya!

21
00:00:52,291 --> 00:00:55,500
♪

22
00:02:40,041 --> 00:02:42,250
[monitor beeping]

23
00:02:45,291 --> 00:02:46,416
Takuya.

24
00:02:47,916 --> 00:02:49,916
[GEEK] You two were the ones
who told him to go to Lost

25
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,125
in the first place!

26
00:02:51,208 --> 00:02:53,208
This is all your fault!

27
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:55,541
What the hell are
the Tama-Shi, anyway?

28
00:02:55,625 --> 00:02:57,958
You knew this would happen,
didn't you?

29
00:02:58,041 --> 00:03:00,458
The whole time, you knew
that Takuya might die!

30
00:03:00,541 --> 00:03:02,583
You better take responsibility!

31
00:03:04,125 --> 00:03:05,166
[YUMIKO]
Listen, Geek.

32
00:03:06,375 --> 00:03:08,791
You need to go into hiding
until things cool off.

33
00:03:08,875 --> 00:03:10,541
Huh? What did I do?

34
00:03:10,625 --> 00:03:13,125
[YUMIKO] You infiltrated
the lock-down district, too.

35
00:03:13,208 --> 00:03:14,916
The police will know by now.

36
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,583
If you stick around here,

37
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:19,000
they'll track you down
and start asking questions.

38
00:03:20,083 --> 00:03:22,125
Do you really think
I'd leave him behind?

39
00:03:22,208 --> 00:03:24,375
[EIJI] Then come stay
with me at my place.

40
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:28,291
Look, I'm not trying
to redeem myself or anything.

41
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:31,083
But at least I know
you'll be safe there.

42
00:03:38,250 --> 00:03:40,083
You should come with us, too.

43
00:03:40,166 --> 00:03:41,208
[KIKYO]
Ready to go?

44
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:44,458
[YUMIKO]
Make up your own mind, Yuki.

45
00:03:46,375 --> 00:03:47,541
After all...

46
00:03:48,541 --> 00:03:51,041
this is the result
of your actions.

47
00:03:51,125 --> 00:03:54,541
[footsteps fading]

48
00:03:54,625 --> 00:03:56,000
[car door closes]

49
00:03:59,125 --> 00:04:00,500
-[RYOKO] Excuse us.
-[EIJI] Hmm?

50
00:04:04,416 --> 00:04:06,083
I'm Ryoko Negishi.

51
00:04:06,166 --> 00:04:07,458
An investigator.

52
00:04:07,541 --> 00:04:08,625
I'm Aoyama.

53
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:11,041
Can we help you?

54
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:13,291
Did you have anything to do
with the second Lost

55
00:04:13,375 --> 00:04:14,583
that transpired this morning?

56
00:04:15,625 --> 00:04:17,416
What makes you think
she's involved with it?

57
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,125
And I believe
this morning's phenomenon

58
00:04:19,208 --> 00:04:21,166
is a bit different
from the Lost.

59
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:23,541
[SYUNPEI] Maybe so, but that's
what the media's calling it.

60
00:04:24,541 --> 00:04:27,000
[RYOKO] This image was captured
near the time of the event

61
00:04:27,083 --> 00:04:30,166
by a surveillance camera
within the lock-down district.

62
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:32,541
Young lady,
there's no mistaking

63
00:04:32,625 --> 00:04:34,458
that you're the one
in this picture.

64
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:35,625
As for the man...

65
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:37,458
He's in intensive care.

66
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:38,791
No visitors allowed.

67
00:04:38,875 --> 00:04:40,625
At the risk of sounding callous,

68
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:43,125
he should have known
how dangerous that area is.

69
00:04:43,208 --> 00:04:44,625
Just what were the two
of you doing over

70
00:04:44,708 --> 00:04:45,958
in the lock-down district?

71
00:04:46,041 --> 00:04:47,541
A mistake.

72
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:49,541
They were out on a date
and accidentally wound up

73
00:04:49,625 --> 00:04:51,041
where they shouldn't have been.

74
00:04:51,125 --> 00:04:53,291
I assume you're in high school,
aren't ya?

75
00:04:53,375 --> 00:04:54,625
You got student ID?

76
00:04:54,708 --> 00:04:56,166
What school are you enrolled in?

77
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,625
This poor girl.

78
00:04:58,708 --> 00:04:59,833
Her whole family vanished

79
00:04:59,916 --> 00:05:01,416
three years ago
during the Lost.

80
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:04,083
The trauma made it hard
for her to attend school,

81
00:05:04,166 --> 00:05:05,791
so she's stayed home
ever since.

82
00:05:05,875 --> 00:05:08,416
Of course, we've kept her
on top of her studies.

83
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,791
But I guess dates aren't
too traumatic for you, huh?

84
00:05:10,875 --> 00:05:12,125
Hey, back off.

85
00:05:12,208 --> 00:05:13,666
She's not allowed
to have any fun?

86
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:16,916
Have you been eating all right?
You look so frail.

87
00:05:20,958 --> 00:05:22,166
Seriously?

88
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:23,833
You're gonna let 'em go,
just like that?

89
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:26,125
I bet the ladies love you.

90
00:05:27,291 --> 00:05:29,458
[SYUNPEI]
What's that supposed to mean?

91
00:05:29,541 --> 00:05:32,291
[keyboards clacking]

92
00:05:32,375 --> 00:05:33,958
[YUKI]
I don't understand.

93
00:05:34,041 --> 00:05:37,000
Why can't we just
tell them the truth?

94
00:05:37,083 --> 00:05:38,791
The Agency's everywhere.

95
00:05:38,875 --> 00:05:40,250
We can't trust anyone.

96
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:42,666
They've infiltrated every part
of the government.

97
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:44,875
The police are no exception.

98
00:05:47,291 --> 00:05:48,791
[GEEK]
Huh? Are you kidding?

99
00:05:48,875 --> 00:05:50,250
You live here?

100
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:53,333
[EIJI] I guess it's kinda big
for a single guy.

101
00:05:53,416 --> 00:05:54,791
Well, come in.

102
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:58,166
[RYOKO] Presenting
my special mirin rice!

103
00:05:58,250 --> 00:06:01,291
There's plenty to go around,
so please help yourselves!

104
00:06:01,375 --> 00:06:04,208
Man, something about this rice
is addictive as hell.

105
00:06:04,291 --> 00:06:06,125
Oh, yeah, it's great.

106
00:06:07,791 --> 00:06:10,958
[YUJI] I don't know what secret
project you guys are working on.

107
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:13,208
But you could learn a thing
or two from her.

108
00:06:13,291 --> 00:06:15,666
She may be young,
but there's a reason

109
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,833
-she was promoted to lieutenant.
-Here!

110
00:06:17,916 --> 00:06:20,208
And her old man was
a legendary police officer,

111
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:21,666
so it makes sense.

112
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:27,083
♪

113
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:28,666
[shuddering breaths]

114
00:06:30,916 --> 00:06:36,875
♪

115
00:06:36,958 --> 00:06:38,083
[gasps]

116
00:06:38,166 --> 00:06:42,375
♪

117
00:06:45,458 --> 00:06:46,583
[YUKI]
Souma.

118
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:56,000
♪

119
00:06:56,083 --> 00:07:00,500
[inaudible dialogue]

120
00:07:00,583 --> 00:07:03,458
♪

121
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:13,583
[inaudible dialogue]

122
00:07:13,666 --> 00:07:19,208
♪

123
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:29,333
[SUZUNA]
How admirable of you.

124
00:07:29,416 --> 00:07:30,416
[YUMIKO]
Suzuna!

125
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:32,416
How did you find us?

126
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:35,416
I assume you've come here
to finish us off, then?

127
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:38,166
I can erase you whenever I want.

128
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:39,541
The same goes for him.

129
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,333
[YUMIKO gasps]

130
00:07:42,666 --> 00:07:45,708
[YUMIKO] Last time, you said
something strange to me.

131
00:07:45,791 --> 00:07:48,000
That you shouldn't overwrite
things any further.

132
00:07:49,041 --> 00:07:50,416
What does that mean?

133
00:07:52,125 --> 00:07:53,458
Well, since you asked,

134
00:07:53,541 --> 00:07:55,416
there is something
you might like to know.

135
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:58,208
[YOSHIAKI]
And now,

136
00:07:58,291 --> 00:08:00,875
I'm going to make this car
completely disappear!

137
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:03,250
[AUDIENCE applauding
and cheering]

138
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:04,875
[YOSHIAKI]
Ready?

139
00:08:04,958 --> 00:08:06,291
One!

140
00:08:06,375 --> 00:08:07,791
Two.

141
00:08:07,875 --> 00:08:09,083
Three!

142
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:14,708
[MALE HOST]
Unbelievable!

143
00:08:14,791 --> 00:08:16,708
Let's give it up
for the renowned magician

144
00:08:16,791 --> 00:08:18,500
Mr. Yoshiaki!

145
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:20,208
Wow, what a performance!

146
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:22,708
I saw a magician make
a tiger disappear once.

147
00:08:24,625 --> 00:08:25,875
[YOSHIAKI gasps]

148
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:29,500
[turning pages]

149
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:38,125
-[slurps]
-[YOSHIAKI] Excuse me.

150
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:40,041
-But who are you?
-Shit! That's hot!

151
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:46,916
Hidaka Detective Agency.

152
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,750
Keigo Hidaka.

153
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,291
What's this?

154
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:52,708
Sorry to bother ya,
but I've been investigating

155
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:55,375
a certain children's institution
for a few years now.

156
00:08:55,458 --> 00:08:59,375
The Light of Hope Academy
for Disabled Children.

157
00:08:59,458 --> 00:09:01,833
I got confirmation
that you attended there.

158
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:03,458
So we can skip over that part.

159
00:09:03,541 --> 00:09:04,625
Yeah, so what?

160
00:09:04,708 --> 00:09:06,375
Gonna sell that info
to a tabloid?

161
00:09:06,458 --> 00:09:08,666
-Be my guest.
-No, no, no.

162
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:10,625
I'm not trying
to get some kinda payoff.

163
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:12,916
Actually, I am here
to help you out.

164
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,291
Mr. Yoshiaki, tell me this.

165
00:09:16,291 --> 00:09:19,250
Are you still searching for that
long-lost big brother of yours?

166
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:21,916
You both grew up
in the same institution.

167
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,166
His name was Tsubasa, right?

168
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:26,333
I bet if you called out
to him publicly on TV,

169
00:09:26,416 --> 00:09:27,791
you'd get a lot of responses.

170
00:09:27,875 --> 00:09:31,291
Not to mention
an increase in viewers.

171
00:09:31,375 --> 00:09:33,333
But if you did that,
it just might hurt ya

172
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:35,166
more than help ya, wouldn't it?

173
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:37,291
Because of who
your big brother is.

174
00:09:37,375 --> 00:09:40,208
You certainly did your homework,
didn't you, Detective?

175
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:43,916
[KEIGO]
My price is 500,000 yen.

176
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,083
I thought you weren't
interested in money.

177
00:09:46,166 --> 00:09:48,291
Yeah, but a man's
gotta earn something.

178
00:09:48,375 --> 00:09:51,541
Don't give up on me yet,
hear what I'm offerin' first.

179
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:53,166
[screams in pain]

180
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:55,541
You wouldn't be racketeering
again, now would you, Keigo?

181
00:09:55,625 --> 00:09:57,291
You've got the wrong idea!

182
00:09:57,375 --> 00:09:58,666
Please let me go!

183
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:04,125
[KEIGO]
You're a civil servant.

184
00:10:04,208 --> 00:10:06,916
You don't know how tough it is
striking out on your own.

185
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,500
I thought being a civil servant
was too confining

186
00:10:09,583 --> 00:10:11,708
and self-employment
gave you freedom.

187
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:15,708
[KEIGO] So, has there been
some kind of development?

188
00:10:16,958 --> 00:10:18,958
Is that why you
were lookin' for me?

189
00:10:19,041 --> 00:10:20,750
I'm still not entirely certain

190
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,708
if the Agency
is involved or not.

191
00:10:22,791 --> 00:10:25,333
But I'd like you
to check into this man.

192
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:27,125
He's a freelance courier,

193
00:10:27,208 --> 00:10:30,291
but it seems he used to be
in the same profession as you.

194
00:10:30,375 --> 00:10:32,166
[KEIGO]
Hmm. Hmm?

195
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:33,583
I think I've met him before.

196
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:34,875
[RYOKO]
Perfect!

197
00:10:34,958 --> 00:10:36,916
So can you do
a little digging for me?

198
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,166
[KEIGO] As if I could ever
say no to you.

199
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:42,000
But, Ryoko,
don't be reckless with this.

200
00:10:42,083 --> 00:10:43,250
[RYOKO]
Same to you, Keigo.

201
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,250
[door opens, closes]

202
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:46,833
Good grief.

203
00:10:46,916 --> 00:10:49,375
That girl is gonna work me
to death one of these days.

204
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,375
[chuckles]

205
00:10:54,458 --> 00:10:56,541
But she is a chip
off the ol' block.

206
00:10:58,125 --> 00:11:01,000
[groaning]

207
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:04,208
You're awake!

208
00:11:04,291 --> 00:11:05,750
[TAKUYA]
Where is he?

209
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:07,958
Kouta?

210
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:10,458
[YUMIKO]
I searched the whole area,

211
00:11:10,541 --> 00:11:12,083
but I couldn't find him.

212
00:11:12,166 --> 00:11:15,250
After that, the second
Lost event happened.

213
00:11:20,458 --> 00:11:21,500
Where's Yuki?

214
00:11:21,583 --> 00:11:22,625
[YUMIKO]
She's fine.

215
00:11:22,708 --> 00:11:24,583
We took her somewhere safe.

216
00:11:26,083 --> 00:11:27,625
That's a relief.

217
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:29,458
Oh, yeah.
That's right.

218
00:11:29,541 --> 00:11:32,833
I meant to ask you, if you know
a producer named Seiji?

219
00:11:32,916 --> 00:11:35,083
[YUMIKO gasps]
What?

220
00:11:35,166 --> 00:11:36,833
How would you
have heard about him?

221
00:11:36,916 --> 00:11:39,708
♪

222
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:46,750
They just announced it
a minute ago.

223
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:48,541
He fell asleep at the wheel.

224
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:50,250
No way.

225
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:52,458
I finally find
a freakin' clue to Lost,

226
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:54,083
and he suddenly
turns up dead?

227
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:57,333
[YUMIKO]
Listen to me.

228
00:11:58,541 --> 00:12:00,208
Please don't go back to Lost.

229
00:12:00,291 --> 00:12:01,583
Stay away from there.

230
00:12:02,750 --> 00:12:03,875
I couldn't take it.

231
00:12:04,875 --> 00:12:06,750
I don't want to see you
get hurt again.

232
00:12:08,125 --> 00:12:11,083
You might not even come out
of there alive next time.

233
00:12:12,333 --> 00:12:13,541
I understand.

234
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:14,750
Really.

235
00:12:15,875 --> 00:12:18,208
But I'm not backing out
of the contract.

236
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:26,666
[RYOKO] My apologies
for barging in like this.

237
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:28,750
But I brought you some lunch.

238
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:30,458
Well, you hungry?

239
00:12:32,125 --> 00:12:34,083
I give humble thanks
for this food.

240
00:12:37,625 --> 00:12:38,875
Mmm.

241
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:40,291
Not too shabby.

242
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:43,000
I like to add mirin to the rice,
but I ran out.

243
00:12:43,083 --> 00:12:45,166
It's normally
a lot tastier than this.

244
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:49,041
I read up on your father, Yuki.

245
00:12:49,125 --> 00:12:51,416
He seemed like
a really amazing man.

246
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:53,666
[YUKI]
You think so, huh?

247
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:56,083
The premier authority
on applied physics.

248
00:12:56,166 --> 00:12:59,000
The director of Japan's
research institute.

249
00:12:59,083 --> 00:13:00,750
It's all impressive.

250
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:03,500
I studied the arts, so I'm
clueless about that stuff.

251
00:13:05,916 --> 00:13:08,708
You know, my father
was also caught in the Lost.

252
00:13:10,208 --> 00:13:12,833
Day after day,
work, work, work.

253
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:15,125
Of course, I knew that being
a police officer meant

254
00:13:15,208 --> 00:13:16,916
he'd be busy
most of the time.

255
00:13:18,041 --> 00:13:20,250
But I missed him,
and I was lonely.

256
00:13:23,583 --> 00:13:25,583
-[YOUNG YUKI] Have a safe trip!
-[DAICHI] Sure thing.

257
00:13:25,666 --> 00:13:27,625
Be back soon.
So anyway...

258
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:29,041
[door closes]

259
00:13:31,208 --> 00:13:34,291
[SOUMA] We were supposed to ride
roller coasters tomorrow.

260
00:13:34,375 --> 00:13:36,333
He keeps breaking his promises.

261
00:13:37,333 --> 00:13:38,916
It hurts my feelings.

262
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,666
Souma, Dad's gotta work
extra hard

263
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:44,041
because everybody
is counting on him.

264
00:13:44,125 --> 00:13:46,000
Try to be patient, okay?

265
00:13:52,625 --> 00:13:54,791
[RYOKO] I wish he'd had
more time for us.

266
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:57,541
But still, I admired
his dedication.

267
00:13:57,625 --> 00:13:59,291
I wanted to be just like him.

268
00:13:59,375 --> 00:14:01,250
To be respected like he was.

269
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:02,625
And so,

270
00:14:02,708 --> 00:14:05,041
after my father got
caught up in the Lost,

271
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:08,208
instead of just feeling sad,
I felt frustrated too.

272
00:14:10,125 --> 00:14:12,833
I'd followed in his footsteps
and become a cop,

273
00:14:12,916 --> 00:14:15,583
hoping I could actually
work with him.

274
00:14:15,666 --> 00:14:18,875
But then, all of a sudden,
he was gone.

275
00:14:18,958 --> 00:14:21,333
It's been three years
since the Lost,

276
00:14:21,416 --> 00:14:23,625
and I know there are
a lot of people who've given up.

277
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:26,458
But not me.

278
00:14:26,541 --> 00:14:29,083
I will never give up.

279
00:14:29,166 --> 00:14:32,125
I believe that my father
is still alive somewhere.

280
00:14:41,416 --> 00:14:45,125
[YUKI crying]

281
00:14:54,583 --> 00:14:56,166
[YUKI]
It's good.

282
00:14:56,250 --> 00:14:57,250
Thanks.

283
00:14:57,333 --> 00:15:00,375
[jet passing overhead]

284
00:15:07,458 --> 00:15:10,125
Okay, so where
are we off to now?

285
00:15:10,208 --> 00:15:11,375
Hey, wait.

286
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:14,000
Isn't this Lacuna's
research facility?

287
00:15:14,083 --> 00:15:15,291
[RYOKO]
I gotta go.

288
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:16,833
[YUKI]
Um...

289
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:18,041
before you leave...

290
00:15:19,583 --> 00:15:21,416
listen to my story.

291
00:15:22,666 --> 00:15:26,166
Ryoko, I want
to tell you everything.

292
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:29,583
About where I was...
and what was done to me.

293
00:15:30,875 --> 00:15:32,125
[RYOKO]
Unforgivable.

294
00:15:32,208 --> 00:15:36,875
♪

295
00:15:36,958 --> 00:15:38,750
How much longer?

296
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:40,416
[footsteps approaching]

297
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:45,958
[TSUKI]
I apologize for the wait.

298
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:49,166
Hello there.

299
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:52,416
I'm the head of public relations
for Lacuna Chemical.

300
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:54,791
And we're from the first
division of investigations.

301
00:15:54,875 --> 00:15:56,208
Pleasure to meet you.

302
00:15:56,291 --> 00:15:58,833
[TSUKI] How can I be
of service to you today?

303
00:16:00,083 --> 00:16:01,125
Just following up.

304
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:02,500
We heard there was a burglary

305
00:16:02,583 --> 00:16:04,791
that took place
at this facility the other day.

306
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:06,333
[TSUKI]
Indeed there was,

307
00:16:06,416 --> 00:16:09,000
but we've already filed
a report with the police.

308
00:16:09,083 --> 00:16:12,041
-Was there some sort of problem?
-No problem.

309
00:16:12,125 --> 00:16:14,458
But do you mind if I take
a look around the place?

310
00:16:14,541 --> 00:16:17,291
We have a strict
confidentiality policy here,

311
00:16:17,375 --> 00:16:18,875
so I'm afraid
I can't allow that.

312
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:21,125
But if you have
a search warrant,

313
00:16:21,208 --> 00:16:22,791
you'll have
our full cooperation.

314
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:27,041
[playing "Moonlight Sonata"]

315
00:16:31,166 --> 00:16:32,583
[knocking on door]

316
00:16:32,666 --> 00:16:34,458
-It's open.
-[door opens]

317
00:16:34,541 --> 00:16:36,000
[TSUKI]
Pardon the interruption.

318
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,541
[TAIYO]
Do we have a guest?

319
00:16:37,625 --> 00:16:40,125
[TSUKI] The police came by
asking questions.

320
00:16:40,208 --> 00:16:41,750
It might be nothing
to worry about,

321
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:43,208
but there's
a slight possibility

322
00:16:43,291 --> 00:16:45,125
that they've encountered
the test subject.

323
00:16:46,125 --> 00:16:47,291
[TAIYO]
Oh?

324
00:16:47,375 --> 00:16:49,958
How long do you plan
on ignoring her?

325
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:52,166
Just look at
what's become of Souma.

326
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:54,625
[TAIYO] I see more potential
in the older sister.

327
00:16:55,791 --> 00:16:58,041
She was able to create
a Lost-like phenomenon

328
00:16:58,125 --> 00:16:59,958
without the use
of an artifact.

329
00:17:00,041 --> 00:17:02,208
I'm curious to see
what else she'll do

330
00:17:02,291 --> 00:17:04,083
while she's roaming free.

331
00:17:04,166 --> 00:17:06,041
[TSUKI] If she becomes
an obstacle to our plans,

332
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:07,583
I'll have her eliminated.

333
00:17:07,666 --> 00:17:08,833
Keep that in mind.

334
00:17:10,291 --> 00:17:11,916
That's awfully harsh of you.

335
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:14,250
Put a cap on your curiosity.

336
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:16,916
[continues playing
"Moonlight Sonata"]

337
00:17:20,458 --> 00:17:21,750
[CHIEF]
What were you thinking?

338
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,500
Stay clear of that area!

339
00:17:23,583 --> 00:17:26,000
That's a direct order
from our superiors, got it?

340
00:17:26,083 --> 00:17:28,250
Don't make me repeat myself!

341
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:30,666
Just do your job
and stay out of trouble!

342
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:32,250
What do you mean "that area"?

343
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:36,125
If you keep on meddling,
I won't be able to protect you.

344
00:17:36,208 --> 00:17:38,208
I'd just like to add that
none of this was my idea.

345
00:17:38,291 --> 00:17:39,958
I just got dragged
around all day.

346
00:17:40,041 --> 00:17:42,500
[CHIEF] Shut up and get back
to your post.

347
00:17:42,583 --> 00:17:44,000
Uh... yes, sir.

348
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:47,291
See, what did I tell you?

349
00:17:47,375 --> 00:17:49,666
You can't just go
rogue like that.

350
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:52,333
I'm on the right track,
I'm sure of it.

351
00:17:52,416 --> 00:17:54,666
When people start applying
pressure like that,

352
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:57,250
what it usually means is you're
getting closer to the truth.

353
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:59,250
You gotta stop.

354
00:18:02,291 --> 00:18:03,875
Finally.

355
00:18:03,958 --> 00:18:06,583
I think I'll be able to get
my father back now.

356
00:18:06,666 --> 00:18:07,666
And also...

357
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:10,375
♪

358
00:18:10,458 --> 00:18:12,250
That is unforgivable.

359
00:18:12,333 --> 00:18:14,291
Thank you for sharing with me.

360
00:18:14,375 --> 00:18:16,375
[YUKI crying softly]

361
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:18,791
I'm sorry. That must
have been so hard.

362
00:18:19,958 --> 00:18:21,750
But don't you worry, Yuki.

363
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:24,458
I'm going to drag the Agency
out into the light.

364
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:27,083
I made a promise.

365
00:18:27,166 --> 00:18:32,583
♪

366
00:18:37,958 --> 00:18:38,916
Whoa, I'm sorry.

367
00:18:39,958 --> 00:18:41,416
Hang on. Takuya?

368
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,583
[TAKUYA]
Hey, Yuki.

369
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:47,708
Oh, Takuya, A-are you okay?

370
00:18:47,791 --> 00:18:48,958
Never better.

371
00:18:49,041 --> 00:18:50,583
[GEEK]
You can barely walk, man!

372
00:18:50,666 --> 00:18:52,166
Well, let's go.

373
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:56,291
♪

374
00:18:56,375 --> 00:18:57,416
There it is.

375
00:18:58,458 --> 00:19:00,583
Yep, that's definitely
the guy, all right.

376
00:19:01,916 --> 00:19:03,583
I gotta hand it to you, Ryoko.

377
00:19:04,625 --> 00:19:06,416
You've got killer instincts.

378
00:19:14,666 --> 00:19:16,750
I can't believe
we're wasting our time

379
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:18,583
looking through these
old real estate documents

380
00:19:18,666 --> 00:19:19,750
in the dead of night.

381
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:21,958
Sometime before
the Lost happened,

382
00:19:22,041 --> 00:19:25,000
a certain factory site
was put up for sale,

383
00:19:25,083 --> 00:19:27,708
and Lacuna Chemical
put in a bid for it.

384
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:29,458
They even announced their plans

385
00:19:29,541 --> 00:19:31,958
to make it
a second research facility.

386
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:34,541
Oh, yeah. But wasn't
Sugisawa Industries

387
00:19:34,625 --> 00:19:36,083
actually the highest bidder?

388
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:37,958
Yes, everything changed

389
00:19:38,041 --> 00:19:40,125
after they were caught
in the Lost, though.

390
00:19:40,208 --> 00:19:42,208
It was a lucky break for Lacuna

391
00:19:42,291 --> 00:19:45,250
and of course a huge hit
for Sugisawa Industries.

392
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:48,166
I found it!
This is the contract!

393
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:50,208
According to this,
the highest bidder

394
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:51,708
was Lacuna Chemical,

395
00:19:51,791 --> 00:19:53,000
but they retracted it?

396
00:19:53,083 --> 00:19:55,666
Wait a minute,
the second largest bidder,

397
00:19:55,750 --> 00:19:58,250
Sugisawa Industries,
ended up buying the land?

398
00:19:58,333 --> 00:20:00,625
[SYUNPEI] It's pretty weird
that they'd retract their bid

399
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:01,833
after winning out.

400
00:20:01,916 --> 00:20:03,833
[RYOKO]
And the date of the sale is...

401
00:20:03,916 --> 00:20:06,625
It was right before the Lost!
[gasps]

402
00:20:06,708 --> 00:20:08,958
That means the Agency
knew exactly

403
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,083
when the Lost would happen
and how big it'd be!

404
00:20:12,083 --> 00:20:13,791
I finally have proof!

405
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:15,916
Hey, let's take this document--
[grunts]

406
00:20:28,458 --> 00:20:30,041
[RYOKO gasping]

407
00:20:30,125 --> 00:20:32,125
[SYUNPEI] Well, you should
have listened to the Chief

408
00:20:32,208 --> 00:20:34,125
when he told you
to stay out of it, Lieutenant.

409
00:20:36,375 --> 00:20:39,166
[RYOKO] You're a part of...
of the Agency?

410
00:20:39,250 --> 00:20:40,916
[SYUNPEI]
For what it's worth,

411
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,500
I was just starting to like you.

412
00:20:43,541 --> 00:20:47,000
But I gotta say, that mirin rice
you're so damn proud of?

413
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:50,625
Seriously, it tastes like shit.

414
00:20:50,708 --> 00:20:52,250
I'll be taking this.

415
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:54,875
Excellent work.

416
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:57,708
[RYOKO continues gasping]

417
00:20:57,791 --> 00:20:59,583
[door opens, closes]

418
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:03,208
[car engine revving]

419
00:21:08,166 --> 00:21:09,541
[YUKI]
You wanted to see me?

420
00:21:11,041 --> 00:21:13,291
[YUMIKO] I know things
have been hard for you.

421
00:21:13,375 --> 00:21:15,916
You finally managed
to escape the Agency,

422
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,541
and then you killed
your own brother.

423
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:21,708
However, that's not
what happened.

424
00:21:24,291 --> 00:21:26,208
Well, since you asked,
there is something

425
00:21:26,291 --> 00:21:27,916
I think you'd be interested
to know.

426
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,166
Yuki's brother Souma.

427
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:31,416
He's actually...

428
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:34,000
-[YUMIKO] He's alive.
-[YUKI gasps]

429
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:35,750
♪

430
00:21:35,833 --> 00:21:39,375
[SOUMA groaning]

431
00:21:40,708 --> 00:21:42,125
[YUKI]
He really survived?

432
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:44,625
[YUMIKO] If you continue
to head towards Lost,

433
00:21:44,708 --> 00:21:46,750
he's going to keep on
appearing like that.

434
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:48,250
Do you understand?

435
00:21:48,333 --> 00:21:50,333
It means you'll have to fight
your little brother.

436
00:21:52,208 --> 00:21:54,291
Are you prepared
to do that again?

437
00:21:54,375 --> 00:21:55,791
Because if you're not,

438
00:21:55,875 --> 00:21:58,291
then please leave Takuya
out of this.

439
00:21:58,375 --> 00:21:59,958
[YUKI]
Souma is my brother.

440
00:22:01,541 --> 00:22:02,791
If he's alive...

441
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:05,166
I'll save him!

442
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:43,833
♪

443
00:23:43,916 --> 00:23:46,000
[TAKUYA]
Next Episode, Affection.

